00:45:32,434 --> 00:45:33,834
What the hell were you thinking, Art?

1151
00:45:33,834 --> 00:45:36,133
Oh, come on. Something had to be done.

1152
00:45:36,133 --> 00:45:37,667
I have to say I agree.

1153
00:45:37,667 --> 00:45:38,934
And he's our friend.

1154
00:45:38,934 --> 00:45:41,167
Whatever else on earth is going on,

1155
00:45:41,167 --> 00:45:42,234
He's our friend!

1156
00:45:42,234 --> 00:45:43,334
You sure about that?

1157
00:45:43,334 --> 00:45:44,934
Why are you being so hard on him?

1158
00:45:44,934 --> 00:45:47,634
One of my favorite
people has disappeared.

1159
00:45:47,634 --> 00:45:51,467
Can you get alzheimer's at 35?

1160
00:45:51,467 --> 00:45:54,334
Maybe I'm trying to wake him up.

1161
00:45:54,334 --> 00:45:57,968
Maybe I'm too sad to cry.

1162
00:46:02,267 --> 00:46:05,234
What I said about myself hurt him.

1163
00:46:05,234 --> 00:46:07,667
He struck
back expertly--

1164
00:46:07,667 --> 00:46:10,667
That stuff about stealing life forces?

1165
00:46:10,667 --> 00:46:13,200
I've always wondered about the reasons.

1166
00:46:19,567 --> 00:46:22,868
Well, we still have an
afternoon to kill, right?

1167
00:46:25,033 --> 00:46:26,767
Charades?

1168
00:46:28,968 --> 00:46:31,200
No. John?

1169
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:33,868
I have a charade, and
it is just for you.

1170
00:46:33,868 --> 00:46:34,934
Sandy, come here.

1171
00:46:34,934 --> 00:46:36,734
Come on, come on, come on.

1172
00:46:36,734 --> 00:46:38,234
Okay, this one's for you.

1173
00:46:38,234 --> 00:46:40,234
Ready?

1174
00:46:40,234 --> 00:46:42,434
( Grunts like ape )

1175
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:46,734
( Wolf whistles )

1176
00:46:46,734 --> 00:46:47,868
( Grunting )

1177
00:46:51,200 --> 00:46:53,000
Ooh!

1178
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:54,234
Uhn.

1179
00:46:54,234 --> 00:46:56,200
My first wedding?

1180
00:46:56,200 --> 00:46:57,467
There you go.

1181
00:46:57,467 --> 00:46:58,901
There you go!

1182
00:46:58,901 --> 00:47:01,601
Very good, and I bet at least one of us

1183
00:47:01,601 --> 00:47:02,801
Is your direct descendent.

1184
00:47:02,801 --> 00:47:04,567
And I didn't even send a christmas card.

1185
00:47:04,567 --> 00:47:06,934
Christmas card? What
about a birthday card?

1186
00:47:06,934 --> 00:47:09,234
And don't even get me
started on the candles...

1187
00:47:09,234 --> 00:47:11,234
with the blowing and the ( huffs )

1188
00:47:11,234 --> 00:47:13,133
For years with the blowing.

1189
00:47:15,167 --> 00:47:17,167
Yeah, all right. I tried.

1190
00:47:17,167 --> 00:47:20,434
Well, uh, call me underdeveloped,

1191
00:47:20,434 --> 00:47:22,801
But I'd like to hear more.

1192
00:47:25,033 --> 00:47:26,234
Me too.

1193
00:47:26,234 --> 00:47:27,667
More.

1194
00:47:27,667 --> 00:47:30,033
You double-damn swear
this isn't some cockamamie

1195
00:47:30,033 --> 00:47:32,234
Science fiction story or...

1196
00:47:32,234 --> 00:47:33,601
you're pulling on us?

1197
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:36,133
Next question.

1198
00:47:36,133 --> 00:47:37,601
You--You--You
realize

1199
00:47:37,601 --> 00:47:38,801
This is an invitation

1200
00:47:38,801 --> 00:47:40,968
To men in white suits with happy pills.

1201
00:47:40,968 --> 00:47:42,033
Think about it--

1202
00:47:42,033 --> 00:47:43,868
A mechanism allowing survival

1203
00:47:43,868 --> 00:47:45,267
For thousands of years?

1204
00:47:45,267 --> 00:47:47,534
Run out of room even faster.

1205
00:47:47,534 --> 00:47:49,801
Then we'd have to go to mars as a colony

1206
00:47:49,801 --> 00:47:51,701
As we expanded, as we'd have to.

1207
00:47:51,701 --> 00:47:53,667
I'd like that.

1208
00:47:53,667 --> 00:47:55,634
On a planet of another star.

1209
00:47:55,634 --> 00:47:57,534
I envy you.

1210
00:47:57,534 --> 00:47:59,901
Did you have a pet dinosaur?

1211
00:47:59,901 --> 00:48:02,267
They were a little bit before my time.

1212
00:48:02,267 --> 00:48:03,534
At least something is.

1213
00:48:03,534 --> 00:48:06,601
No doubt you could give us
a thousand details, John,

1214
00:48:06,601 --> 00:48:07,701
Corroborating your story,

1215
00:48:07,701 --> 00:48:10,167
From the magdalene to the Buddha to now.

1216
00:48:10,167 --> 00:48:11,367
Ten thousand,

1217
00:48:11,367 --> 00:48:12,968
And you could stay out of the books.

1218
00:48:12,968 --> 00:48:15,467
Oh, it's getting chilly.

1219
00:48:15,467 --> 00:48:17,667
Here, come over here. Join me.

1220
00:48:20,033 --> 00:48:23,667
That, uh, raises an
interesting question, John.

1221
00:48:23,667 --> 00:48:25,200
Could there be others like you

1222
00:48:25,200 --> 00:48:27,400
Who escaped the aging
process as you have?

1223
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:28,467
Representing something terrific

1224
00:48:28,467 --> 00:48:30,133
We don't even know about biology.

1225
00:48:30,133 --> 00:48:31,167
We're learning all the time.

1226
00:48:31,167 --> 00:48:32,634
Yeah, but how would he know?

1227
00:48:32,634 --> 00:48:35,667
He doesn't wear an I.D. Badge
saying "yabba dabba doo."

1228
00:48:35,667 --> 00:48:38,467
There was a man in the 1600s.

1229
00:48:38,467 --> 00:48:40,934
Where were you in 1292 a.D.?

1230
00:48:40,934 --> 00:48:43,534
Where were you a year ago on this date?

1231
00:48:46,200 --> 00:48:48,968
Anyway, it was the
1600s, and I met a man,

1232
00:48:48,968 --> 00:48:51,701
And I had a hunch that he was...

1233
00:48:51,701 --> 00:48:53,667
like me, so I told him.

1234
00:48:53,667 --> 00:48:57,434
Ah. See, you said this was a first.

1235
00:48:57,434 --> 00:48:58,467
I forgot.

1236
00:48:58,467 --> 00:49:00,334
A crack in your story, John?

1237
00:49:00,334 --> 00:49:01,801
A touch of senility.

1238
00:49:01,801 --> 00:49:04,367
Anyway, he said yes,

1239
00:49:04,367 --> 00:49:06,367
But from another time, another place.

1240
00:49:06,367 --> 00:49:07,934
We talked for two days.

1241
00:49:07,934 --> 00:49:09,901
It was all pretty convincing,

1242
00:49:09,901 --> 00:49:12,200
But we couldn't be sure.

1243
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:14,334
We each confirmed what the other said,

1244
00:49:14,334 --> 00:49:16,734
But how do we know if the confirmation

1245
00:49:16,734 --> 00:49:18,334
Was genuine or an echo?

1246
00:49:18,334 --> 00:49:20,300
I knew I was kosher,

1247
00:49:20,300 --> 00:49:24,200
But I thought, "maybe
he's playing a game on me."

1248
00:49:24,200 --> 00:49:27,634
You know, a scholar
of all we spoke about.

1249
00:49:27,634 --> 00:49:30,667
He said he was inclined
with the same reservation.

1250
00:49:30,667 --> 00:49:31,934
Now, that's interesting.

1251
00:49:31,934 --> 00:49:34,100
Just as we can never be sure,

1252
00:49:34,100 --> 00:49:35,601
Even if we
wanted to--

1253
00:49:35,601 --> 00:49:37,234
I mean, if we were sure,

1254
00:49:37,234 --> 00:49:38,934
You couldn't be sure of that.

1255
00:49:38,934 --> 00:49:41,033
We parted, agreeing
to keep in touch--

1256
00:49:41,033 --> 00:49:42,501
Of course,
we didn't--

1257
00:49:42,501 --> 00:49:44,968
And 200 years later I thought I saw him

1258
00:49:44,968 --> 00:49:47,234
In a train station in brussels.

1259
00:49:47,234 --> 00:49:48,801
Lost him in the crowd.

1260
00:49:48,801 --> 00:49:51,000
Oh, what a shame.

1261
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:53,067
I--I mean, if
it were true.

1262
00:49:53,067 --> 00:49:54,601
Okay, here's one for you.

1263
00:49:54,601 --> 00:49:56,901
What do you do in your spare time?

1264
00:49:56,901 --> 00:49:58,067
( Laughs )

1265
00:49:58,067 --> 00:49:59,200
Every 50 years or so,

1266
00:49:59,200 --> 00:50:01,100
When I wanna get away from the rush,

1267
00:50:01,100 --> 00:50:03,133
I go down to a primitive
tribe in new guinea

1268
00:50:03,133 --> 00:50:05,868
Where I'm worshipped as an immortal god,

1269
00:50:05,868 --> 00:50:08,267
And they have a huge statue of me.

1270
00:50:08,267 --> 00:50:09,501
It's a big party.

1271
00:50:09,501 --> 00:50:11,567
Yeah, I've got a lot of pictures of it,

1272
00:50:11,567 --> 00:50:13,434
But I've already packed
them up. I'm sorry.

1273
00:50:13,434 --> 00:50:17,167
I won't make the obvious nasty
crack about more unwashed cavemen.

1274
00:50:17,167 --> 00:50:18,567
Actually, bathing was the style

1275
00:50:18,567 --> 00:50:20,434
Until the middle ages
when the church told us

1276
00:50:20,434 --> 00:50:23,300
It was sinful to wash away god's dirt,

1277
00:50:23,300 --> 00:50:24,567
So people were sewn

1278
00:50:24,567 --> 00:50:26,067
Into their underwear in october

1279
00:50:26,067 --> 00:50:27,868
And they popped out in april.

1280
00:50:27,868 --> 00:50:29,667
You said you just happened.

1281
00:50:29,667 --> 00:50:31,734
I don't believe that.

1282
00:50:31,734 --> 00:50:33,367
If your story's true,

1283
00:50:33,367 --> 00:50:37,033
Why did god allow you to happen?

1284
00:50:37,033 --> 00:50:39,200
That makes an interesting point.

1285
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:40,901
Are you religious, John?

1286
00:50:40,901 --> 00:50:43,434
I don't follow a known religion. No.

1287
00:50:43,434 --> 00:50:44,534
Ever.

1288
00:50:44,534 --> 00:50:46,834
Long time ago I did,

1289
00:50:46,834 --> 00:50:49,100
Like most people.

1290
00:50:49,100 --> 00:50:50,901
Some just never get over it.

1291
00:50:50,901 --> 00:50:52,300
Do you believe in god?

1292
00:50:53,400 --> 00:50:55,200
As laplace said,

1293
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:57,834
"I have no need of that hypothesis."

1294
00:50:57,834 --> 00:50:59,400
He may be around, though.

1295
00:50:59,400 --> 00:51:02,000
He's everywhere. We just can't see him.

1296
00:51:02,000 --> 00:51:04,701
Pfft. If this was the best I could do,

1297
00:51:04,701 --> 00:51:06,133
I'd be hiding, too.

1298
00:51:06,133 --> 00:51:07,767
And creation...

1299
00:51:07,767 --> 00:51:10,100
it's here--I'm not so
sure it was created.

1300
00:51:10,100 --> 00:51:11,467
What then?

1301
00:51:11,467 --> 00:51:15,033
Maybe it's just accumulated,
fields affecting fields.

1302
00:51:15,033 --> 00:51:17,701
What about the source
of the field energies?

1303
00:51:17,701 --> 00:51:19,701
Wouldn't that imply a prime mover?

1304
00:51:19,701 --> 00:51:21,834
I'd wonder about the
source of the prime mover,

1305
00:51:21,834 --> 00:51:25,033
Infinite regress, but that
doesn't imply anything to me.

1306
00:51:25,033 --> 00:51:26,834
Back to the mystery.

1307
00:51:26,834 --> 00:51:28,901
It's a very old question,

1308
00:51:28,901 --> 00:51:32,767
But there's no answer
except in religious terms.

1309
00:51:32,767 --> 00:51:35,534
If you have faith, it's answered.

1310
00:51:35,534 --> 00:51:38,968
Did you ever meet any person
from our religious history?

1311
00:51:38,968 --> 00:51:41,033
A biblical figure?

1312
00:51:41,033 --> 00:51:42,367
In a way.

1313
00:51:42,367 --> 00:51:44,100
Who?

1314
00:51:44,100 --> 00:51:45,601
We should skip this one.

1315
00:51:45,601 --> 00:51:47,300
No, no, no skipping. Come on.

1316
00:51:47,300 --> 00:51:48,367
Next question.

1317
00:51:48,367 --> 00:51:49,767
No, come on!

1318
00:51:49,767 --> 00:51:51,334
( Clamoring )

1319
00:51:51,334 --> 00:51:52,634
Come on, spit it out!

1320
00:51:52,634 --> 00:51:54,300
Good lord! You were one of them!

1321
00:51:54,300 --> 00:51:57,934
This is going in a direction
that I--I didn't expect.

1322
00:51:57,934 --> 00:52:00,734
I hoped it wouldn't--
We...call it a night.

1323
00:52:00,734 --> 00:52:04,334
Come on! You were someone
in religious history?

1324
00:52:04,334 --> 00:52:05,601
Yes.

1325
00:52:05,601 --> 00:52:07,133
In the bible?

1326
00:52:07,133 --> 00:52:08,133
Yes.

1327
00:52:08,133 --> 00:52:09,200
Someone we know?

1328
00:52:09,200 --> 00:52:11,234
How could we not know
someone in the bible?

1329
00:52:11,234 --> 00:52:12,434
I mean somebody important.

1330
00:52:12,434 --> 00:52:14,133
You may think you know him,

1331
00:52:14,133 --> 00:52:15,701
But it's mostly myth.

1332
00:52:15,701 --> 00:52:19,167
The entire bible is
mostly myth and allegory

1333
00:52:19,167 --> 00:52:22,400
With maybe some basis
in historical events.

1334
00:52:22,400 --> 00:52:26,734
You were part of that history?

1335
00:52:26,734 --> 00:52:27,834
Yes.

1336
00:52:28,968 --> 00:52:30,234
Moses.

1337
00:52:30,234 --> 00:52:34,067
Moses was based on misis, a syrian myth,

1338
00:52:34,067 --> 00:52:35,634
And there are
earlier versions--

1339
00:52:35,634 --> 00:52:37,767
All found floating on water,

1340
00:52:37,767 --> 00:52:40,200
The staff that changed to a snake,

1341
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:42,834
Waters that were parted so followers

1342
00:52:42,834 --> 00:52:44,667
Could be led to freedom

1343
00:52:44,667 --> 00:52:45,934
And even receive laws

1344
00:52:45,934 --> 00:52:47,501
On stone or wooden tablets.

1345
00:52:47,501 --> 00:52:50,434
One of the apostles.

1346
00:52:50,434 --> 00:52:53,100
They weren't really apostles.

1347
00:52:53,100 --> 00:52:55,267
They didn't do any real teaching.

1348
00:52:55,267 --> 00:52:58,567
Peter the fisherman learned
a little more about fishing.

1349
00:52:58,567 --> 00:53:00,601
How do you know that?

1350
00:53:03,033 --> 00:53:06,000
The mythical overlay is so enormous...

1351
00:53:07,400 --> 00:53:09,467
and not good.

1352
00:53:09,467 --> 00:53:15,667
The truth is so, so simple.

1353
00:53:15,667 --> 00:53:19,367
The new testament in 100
words or less. You ready?

1354
00:53:19,367 --> 00:53:20,801
I don't think I wanna hear this.

1355
00:53:20,801 --> 00:53:22,534
Harry, will you take me home?

1356
00:53:22,534 --> 00:53:24,400
No, not right now. I
do want to hear this.

1357
00:53:24,400 --> 00:53:26,767
Sit down, Edith. You
act like you believe him.

1358
00:53:26,767 --> 00:53:28,200
It's sacrilege.

1359
00:53:28,200 --> 00:53:29,434
How can it be sacrilege?

1360
00:53:29,434 --> 00:53:30,567
He hasn't said anything yet.

1361
00:53:30,567 --> 00:53:33,267
The new new testament is sacrilege.

1362
00:53:33,267 --> 00:53:35,801
There are a dozen new new testaments,

1363
00:53:35,801 --> 00:53:38,934
From hebrew to greek
to latin to tyndale,

1364
00:53:38,934 --> 00:53:40,767
All the way to king james,

1365
00:53:40,767 --> 00:53:42,133
All revisionist,

1366
00:53:42,133 --> 00:53:44,400
And all called revealed truth.

1367
00:53:44,400 --> 00:53:47,601
I mean a new new testament in 100 words.

1368
00:53:47,601 --> 00:53:49,901
I can give you the ten
commandments in ten words.

1369
00:53:49,901 --> 00:53:51,501
Don't. Don't, don't, don't,

1370
00:53:51,501 --> 00:53:53,300
Don't, don't, don't,
don't, don't, don't.

1371
00:53:53,300 --> 00:53:54,934
( Laughs ) Don't.

1372
00:53:54,934 --> 00:53:58,000
The commandments are just modern
updates of more ancient laws.

1373
00:53:58,000 --> 00:53:59,868
Hammurabi's code.

1374
00:53:59,868 --> 00:54:02,367
That's right, they
weren't the first, right?

1375
00:54:02,367 --> 00:54:05,334
Edith, I was raised on the torah...

1376
00:54:05,334 --> 00:54:06,834
my wife, on the koran.

1377
00:54:06,834 --> 00:54:08,601
My oldest son is an atheist.

1378
00:54:08,601 --> 00:54:10,100
My youngest is a scientologist.

1379
00:54:10,100 --> 00:54:12,133
My daughter is studying hinduism.

1380
00:54:12,133 --> 00:54:16,367
I imagine that there is room there
for a holy war in my living room,

1381
00:54:16,367 --> 00:54:18,567
But we practice live and let live.

1382
00:54:19,901 --> 00:54:21,334
Why don't you sit down.

1383
00:54:28,434 --> 00:54:31,367
What is your preferred
version of the bible?

1384
00:54:31,367 --> 00:54:32,868
The King James, of course.

1385
00:54:32,868 --> 00:54:35,334
It's the most modern, the
work of great scholars.

1386
00:54:35,334 --> 00:54:36,834
Modern is good.

1387
00:54:38,634 --> 00:54:40,868
All right, John, hit
us with the short form.

1388
00:54:42,901 --> 00:54:44,934
Guy met the Buddha, liked what he heard,

1389
00:54:44,934 --> 00:54:46,667
Thought about
it for a while--

1390
00:54:46,667 --> 00:54:48,567
Say 500 years, while he returned

1391
00:54:48,567 --> 00:54:49,834
To the Mediterranean,

1392
00:54:49,834 --> 00:54:52,534
Became an etruscan.

1393
00:54:52,534 --> 00:54:54,167
Seeped into the roman empire.

1394
00:54:54,167 --> 00:54:55,968
He didn't like
what they became--

1395
00:54:55,968 --> 00:54:58,234
A giant killing machine.

1396
00:54:58,234 --> 00:54:59,968
He went to the near east thinking,

1397
00:54:59,968 --> 00:55:03,234
"Why not pass the Buddha's
teachings on in a modern form."

1398
00:55:03,234 --> 00:55:05,501
So he tried.

1399
00:55:05,501 --> 00:55:07,667
One dissident against rome?

1400
00:55:07,667 --> 00:55:08,868
Rome won.

1401
00:55:08,868 --> 00:55:10,267
The rest is history.

1402
00:55:10,267 --> 00:55:12,734
Well, sort of. Lot of
fairy tales mixed in.

1403
00:55:15,567 --> 00:55:17,567
I knew it.

1404
00:55:17,567 --> 00:55:19,868
He's saying he was Christ.

1405
00:55:19,868 --> 00:55:21,434
Oh, no. That's the medal

1406
00:55:21,434 --> 00:55:23,767
They pinned on Jesus
to fulfill prophecy.

1407
00:55:23,767 --> 00:55:25,000
The crucifixion.

1408
00:55:25,000 --> 00:55:28,000
He blocked the pain
as he had learned to do

1409
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:29,400
In tibet and india.

1410
00:55:29,400 --> 00:55:31,801
He also learned to
slow his body processes

1411
00:55:31,801 --> 00:55:34,400
Down to the point where
they were undetectable.

1412
00:55:34,400 --> 00:55:35,834
They thought he was dead.

1413
00:55:35,834 --> 00:55:37,234
So his followers pulled him

1414
00:55:37,234 --> 00:55:39,567
From the cross, placed him in a cave...

1415
00:55:39,567 --> 00:55:42,200
his body normalized as
he had trained it to...

1416
00:55:43,467 --> 00:55:46,000
he attempted to go away undetected,

1417
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:48,400
But some devotees were standing watch.

1418
00:55:49,834 --> 00:55:52,234
Tried to explain.

1419
00:55:52,234 --> 00:55:54,734
They were ecstatic.

1420
00:55:54,734 --> 00:55:57,234
Thus, I was resurrected,

1421
00:55:57,234 --> 00:55:59,033
And I ascended to central europe

1422
00:55:59,033 --> 00:56:01,267
To get away as far as possible.

1423
00:56:01,267 --> 00:56:03,734
You don't mean a word of this, John.

1424
00:56:03,734 --> 00:56:05,734
My god, why are you doing this?

1425
00:56:05,734 --> 00:56:07,300
Let me see your wrists.

1426
00:56:07,300 --> 00:56:08,801
I don't scar.

1427
00:56:08,801 --> 00:56:10,467
Besides, they tied me...

1428
00:56:10,467 --> 00:56:13,767
but nails and blood make
better religious Art.

1429
00:56:13,767 --> 00:56:16,801
( Laughs ) all the
speculations about Jesus.

1430
00:56:16,801 --> 00:56:18,601
He was black, he was asian,

1431
00:56:18,601 --> 00:56:21,567
He was a blue-eyed
Aryan with a golden beard

1432
00:56:21,567 --> 00:56:23,567
And hair straight out
of vidal sassoon's,

1433
00:56:23,567 --> 00:56:26,734
He was a benevolent alien,
he never existed at all.

1434
00:56:26,734 --> 00:56:28,901
Now he's a caveman.

1435
00:56:28,901 --> 00:56:32,000
The Christ figure goes all
the way back to Krishna--

1436
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:33,067
Hercules, of course.

1437
00:56:33,067 --> 00:56:34,133
Hercules?

1438
00:56:34,133 --> 00:56:36,267
Born of a virgin, Alcmene.

1439
00:56:36,267 --> 00:56:39,467
A god for a father, Zeus.

1440
00:56:39,467 --> 00:56:42,133
The only begotten.

1441
00:56:42,133 --> 00:56:44,734
<i>The savior--
The greek? Soter.</i>

1442
00:56:44,734 --> 00:56:46,901
The good shepherd, the prince of peace,

1443
00:56:46,901 --> 00:56:49,434
Bringing gentle persuasion
and divine wisdom.

1444
00:56:49,434 --> 00:56:52,834
He died, joined his father on olympus

1445
00:56:52,834 --> 00:56:55,067
A thousand years before gethsemane.

1446
00:56:55,067 --> 00:56:58,934
How can you compare pagan
mythology to the true word?

1447
00:56:58,934 --> 00:57:01,534
Pretty damn closely, I'd say.

1448
00:57:01,534 --> 00:57:04,033
The early Christian leaders,

1449
00:57:04,033 --> 00:57:05,968
They threw away hebrew manuscripts

1450
00:57:05,968 --> 00:57:08,868
And borrowed from pagan
sources all over the place.

1451
00:57:08,868 --> 00:57:11,534
Do you realize how...

1452
00:57:11,534 --> 00:57:13,801
inconsiderately you're
treating my feelings?

1453
00:57:13,801 --> 00:57:17,300
About as inconsiderately
as we're treating John's.

1454
00:57:17,300 --> 00:57:19,601
Well, he doesn't
believe what he's saying!

1455
00:57:19,601 --> 00:57:22,167
Do you believe literally
everything in the bible, Edith?

1456
00:57:22,167 --> 00:57:23,334
Yes!

1457
00:57:23,334 --> 00:57:24,734
Before you say it,

1458
00:57:24,734 --> 00:57:27,400
I know it's undergone a lot of changes,

1459
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:29,901
But god has spoken through man

1460
00:57:29,901 --> 00:57:31,968
To make his word clearer.

1461
00:57:31,968 --> 00:57:34,400
He couldn't get it right the first time?

1462
00:57:34,400 --> 00:57:37,434
We're imperfect! He had to
work to make us understand.

1463
00:57:37,434 --> 00:57:40,801
<i>He couldn't get us right
the first time, Edith?</i>

1464
00:57:40,801 --> 00:57:43,601
Taken alone, the
philosophical teachings of Jesus

1465
00:57:43,601 --> 00:57:45,767
Are buddhism with
a hebrew accent--

1466
00:57:45,767 --> 00:57:49,534
Kindness, tolerance, brotherhood, love,

1467
00:57:49,534 --> 00:57:51,267
A ruthless realism acknowledging

1468
00:57:51,267 --> 00:57:54,501
That life is as it is here
on earth, here and now.

1469
00:57:54,501 --> 00:57:57,067
The kingdom of god, meaning goodness,

1470
00:57:57,067 --> 00:58:00,734
Is right here, where it should be.

1471
00:58:00,734 --> 00:58:02,868
"I am what I am becoming."

1472
00:58:02,868 --> 00:58:04,434
That's what the Buddha brought in.

1473
00:58:04,434 --> 00:58:05,868
And that's what I taught.

1474
00:58:05,868 --> 00:58:08,834
But a talking snake
make a lady eat an apple,

1475
00:58:08,834 --> 00:58:10,000
So we're screwed.

1476
00:58:10,000 --> 00:58:11,567
Heaven and hell were peddled

1477
00:58:11,567 --> 00:58:14,601
So priests could rule
through seduction and terror,

1478
00:58:14,601 --> 00:58:18,067
Save our souls that we never
lost in the first place.

1479
00:58:18,067 --> 00:58:19,734
I threw a clean pass...

1480
00:58:19,734 --> 00:58:21,834
they ran it out of the ballpark.

1481
00:58:21,834 --> 00:58:24,601
This is blasphemy.

1482
00:58:24,601 --> 00:58:26,901
It's horrible! Who else were you?

1483
00:58:26,901 --> 00:58:30,234
Solomon, elvis, jack the ripper?

1484
00:58:30,234 --> 00:58:32,033
It's been said that Buddha and Jesus

1485
00:58:32,033 --> 00:58:33,934
Would laugh or cry if they'd known

1486
00:58:33,934 --> 00:58:35,400
What was done in their name.

1487
00:58:35,400 --> 00:58:37,234
And if there is a creator,

1488
00:58:37,234 --> 00:58:39,000
He'd probably feel the same way.

1489
00:58:39,000 --> 00:58:42,934
I see ceremony, ritual, processions,

1490
00:58:42,934 --> 00:58:45,267
Genuflecting, moaning, intoning,

1491
00:58:45,267 --> 00:58:48,067
Venerating cookies and wine,

1492
00:58:48,067 --> 00:58:49,868
And I think...

1493
00:58:49,868 --> 00:58:51,467
it's not what I had in mind.

1494
00:58:51,467 --> 00:58:52,601
But that's vatican flapdoodle.

1495
00:58:52,601 --> 00:58:55,133
It doesn't have a thing to do with god.

1496
00:58:55,133 --> 00:58:57,534
As you said, John,
everywhere, religions...

1497
00:58:57,534 --> 00:59:01,400
from exalting life to
purging joy as a sin.

1498
00:59:01,400 --> 00:59:04,067
Rome does it as grand opera.

1499
00:59:05,334 --> 00:59:07,133
A simple path to goodness needs

1500
00:59:07,133 --> 00:59:09,100
A supernatural roadmap.

1501
00:59:09,100 --> 00:59:11,267
Supernatural...

1502
00:59:11,267 --> 00:59:13,934
a stupid word, I mean...

1503
00:59:13,934 --> 00:59:15,834
anything that happens,
happens within nature,

1504
00:59:15,834 --> 00:59:17,467
Whether we believe in it or not.

1505
00:59:17,467 --> 00:59:20,067
Like a 14,000-year-old 
caveman.

1506
00:59:20,067 --> 00:59:22,400
( Car approaching )

1507
00:59:28,901 --> 00:59:31,033
I--I--I drove
for a while,

1508
00:59:31,033 --> 00:59:33,200
And then I sat for a while.

1509
00:59:33,200 --> 00:59:34,634
I'm so ashamed.

1510
00:59:34,634 --> 00:59:36,334
( Shivering ) and I'm freezing.

1511
00:59:36,334 --> 00:59:37,634
Well, come inside.

1512
00:59:37,634 --> 00:59:39,767
I still don't believe you, of course.

1513
00:59:39,767 --> 00:59:40,834
You need help.

1514
00:59:40,834 --> 00:59:41,868
Everybody needs help.

1515
00:59:41,868 --> 00:59:43,934
Yes, well, some more than others.

1516
00:59:57,934 --> 01:00:00,133
From the Buddha to the cross,

1517
01:00:00,133 --> 01:00:04,801
I have always imagined
both as entirely mythic--

1518
01:00:04,801 --> 01:00:07,234
But I would like to hear more.

1519
01:00:07,234 --> 01:00:09,934
May I lie on the couch for a moment?

1520
01:00:09,934 --> 01:00:12,567
I'm not as young as I used to be.

1521
01:00:15,267 --> 01:00:16,334
Ohh!

1522
01:00:16,334 --> 01:00:18,434
( Laughs )

1523
01:00:18,434 --> 01:00:22,501
So, you were Jesus.

1524
01:00:22,501 --> 01:00:25,601
Well, perhaps somebody had to
be, for better or for worse.

1525
01:00:25,601 --> 01:00:27,367
The jury is still out.

1526
01:00:27,367 --> 01:00:30,400
When did you begin to
believe you were Jesus?

1527
01:00:30,400 --> 01:00:33,501
When did you begin to believe
you were a psychiatrist?

1528
01:00:33,501 --> 01:00:36,634
Since I graduated harvard medical school

1529
01:00:36,634 --> 01:00:39,334
And finished my residency,
I've had that feeling.

1530
01:00:39,334 --> 01:00:42,200
Oh, I sometimes dream about it.

1531
01:00:42,200 --> 01:00:43,868
Have you acted upon this belief?

1532
01:00:43,868 --> 01:00:46,234
I had a private practice for a while,

1533
01:00:46,234 --> 01:00:47,801
And then I taught.

1534
01:00:47,801 --> 01:00:49,200
Nothing unusual--

1535
01:00:49,200 --> 01:00:52,467
Oh, until one day, I met a caveman

1536
01:00:52,467 --> 01:00:54,567
Who thought he was Jesus.

1537
01:00:54,567 --> 01:00:57,567
Do you find that unusual?

1538
01:00:57,567 --> 01:01:00,000
Very. I would stake my reputation

1539
01:01:00,000 --> 01:01:02,434
He as sane as I am,

1540
01:01:02,434 --> 01:01:05,367
So why does he persist in such a story?

1541
01:01:05,367 --> 01:01:07,534
There must be a reason, though.

1542
01:01:07,534 --> 01:01:09,434
Unless I imagined it all?

1543
01:01:09,434 --> 01:01:10,734
Is that possible?

1544
01:01:10,734 --> 01:01:12,567
I think you're as sane as he is.

1545
01:01:12,567 --> 01:01:13,934
Oh, god, I--

1546
01:01:13,934 --> 01:01:16,033
( Laughs ) no.

1547
01:01:17,567 --> 01:01:20,501
Did you ever find it
prudent to worship yourself

1548
01:01:20,501 --> 01:01:22,300
Rather than be thought a heretic?

1549
01:01:22,300 --> 01:01:23,567
That would be something.

1550
01:01:23,567 --> 01:01:26,100
Other times, christianity
was considered heresy.

1551
01:01:26,100 --> 01:01:27,901
I had to pretend other faiths.

1552
01:01:27,901 --> 01:01:31,968
And what does Jesus have
to say to those present

1553
01:01:31,968 --> 01:01:34,367
Who find it difficult to believe in him?

1554
01:01:34,367 --> 01:01:37,033
Believe in what he tried to teach,

1555
01:01:37,033 --> 01:01:39,000
Without rigmarole.

1556
01:01:39,000 --> 01:01:41,634
Piety is not what the
lessons bring to people.

1557
01:01:41,634 --> 01:01:44,367
It's the mistake they
bring to the lessons.

1558
01:01:51,767 --> 01:01:54,501
Well, it's getting to be night.

1559
01:01:56,000 --> 01:01:58,167
I still have stuff to carry

1560
01:01:58,167 --> 01:02:00,534
And a long drive.

1561
01:02:00,534 --> 01:02:02,100
I'll help.

1562
01:02:02,100 --> 01:02:05,701
John, do you have a 
destination in mind?

1563
01:02:07,067 --> 01:02:08,434
Never mind.

1564
01:02:08,434 --> 01:02:09,834
I won't ask.

1565
01:02:10,901 --> 01:02:11,901
Thank you.

1566
01:02:19,267 --> 01:02:22,133
Anyone mentally ill can imagine

1567
01:02:22,133 --> 01:02:25,100
A fantastic background--
Even an entire life--

1568
01:02:25,100 --> 01:02:27,434
And sincerely believe it.

1569
01:02:27,434 --> 01:02:30,033
The man who thinks he is napoleon

1570
01:02:30,033 --> 01:02:31,934
Does believe it.

1571
01:02:31,934 --> 01:02:34,934
His true identity has taken a backseat

1572
01:02:34,934 --> 01:02:37,767
To his delusion and the need for it.

1573
01:02:37,767 --> 01:02:40,033
If that's the case with John,

1574
01:02:40,033 --> 01:02:41,767
There is a grave disorder.

1575
01:02:41,767 --> 01:02:44,234
Organized brilliantly.

1576
01:02:44,234 --> 01:02:46,334
He's got an answer for everything.

1577
01:02:46,334 --> 01:02:48,968
It might involve
rejection of his father,

1578
01:02:48,968 --> 01:02:50,934
Of his entire early past,

1579
01:02:50,934 --> 01:02:52,300
Replaced by this fantasy.

1580
01:02:52,300 --> 01:02:54,400
He says he can't remember his father.

1581
01:02:54,400 --> 01:02:55,434
Precisely why?

1582
01:02:55,434 --> 01:02:57,000
You said he was sane.

1583
01:02:57,000 --> 01:02:58,300
Did I?

1584
01:02:59,734 --> 01:03:02,200
Do you think that perhaps our caveman

1585
01:03:02,200 --> 01:03:04,000
Has a monkey on his back?

1586
01:03:04,000 --> 01:03:05,634
Drugs?

1587
01:03:05,634 --> 01:03:07,133
No, no, no, no.

1588
01:03:07,133 --> 01:03:09,534
I've done a lot of consulting
work with narcotics.

1589
01:03:09,534 --> 01:03:11,567
I've seen people
tripping, strung out--

1590
01:03:11,567 --> 01:03:13,734
Whatever's up with John, it isn't that.

1591
01:03:13,734 --> 01:03:15,868
I've looked
for signs--None.

1592
01:03:15,868 --> 01:03:17,467
Could cavemen really talk?

1593
01:03:17,467 --> 01:03:19,868
We think that language
came into existence

1594
01:03:19,868 --> 01:03:21,167
60,000 years ago.

1595
01:03:21,167 --> 01:03:23,200
The structure of stone age culture

1596
01:03:23,200 --> 01:03:25,467
Is evidence of the
ability to communicate--

1597
01:03:25,467 --> 01:03:26,901
Verbally.

1598
01:03:26,901 --> 01:03:28,567
( Wolf whistles; clicks )

1599
01:03:28,567 --> 01:03:30,734
Oh, shut up.

1600
01:03:39,901 --> 01:03:42,100
Maybe it'd be easier if I were.

1601
01:03:42,100 --> 01:03:43,267
Crazy?

1602
01:03:44,534 --> 01:03:46,100
No.

1603
01:03:46,100 --> 01:03:49,100
( Coyote howls )

1604
01:03:59,234 --> 01:04:02,000
That is fascinating, isn't it,

1605
01:04:02,000 --> 01:04:05,133
A brave attempt to teach
buddhism in the west.

1606
01:04:05,133 --> 01:04:07,000
It's no wonder he failed.

1607
01:04:07,000 --> 01:04:08,534
We're not ready for it.

1608
01:04:08,534 --> 01:04:10,968
You're talking
as if you believed him.

1609
01:04:10,968 --> 01:04:13,067
Well, it is possible, isn't it?

1610
01:04:13,067 --> 01:04:15,267
I mean, anything is possible.

1611
01:04:15,267 --> 01:04:17,133
Look, we have two simple choices.

1612
01:04:17,133 --> 01:04:19,601
We can get all bent out of shape

1613
01:04:19,601 --> 01:04:21,968
Intellectualizing or
bench-pressing logic,

1614
01:04:21,968 --> 01:04:24,601
Or we can simply relax and enjoy it.

1615
01:04:24,601 --> 01:04:26,434
I can listen critically,

1616
01:04:26,434 --> 01:04:29,801
But I don't have to make
up my mind about anything.

1617
01:04:29,801 --> 01:04:31,300
But you think you do?

1618
01:04:31,300 --> 01:04:34,033
Well, unfortunately, there's
no authorities on prehistory,

1619
01:04:34,033 --> 01:04:35,834
So we couldn't stop him there.

1620
01:04:35,834 --> 01:04:37,634
There are experts on the bible.

1621
01:04:37,634 --> 01:04:39,267
Dream on.

1622
01:04:39,267 --> 01:04:41,601
Yeah, thus the lost years of Jesus.

1623
01:04:41,601 --> 01:04:44,300
He didn't exist until John put on a hat.

1624
01:04:44,300 --> 01:04:48,334
I don't believe in angels and the
nativity and the star in the east,

1625
01:04:48,334 --> 01:04:51,467
But there are stories about
the childhood of Jesus.

1626
01:04:51,467 --> 01:04:53,901
History hates a vacuum.

1627
01:04:53,901 --> 01:04:56,467
Improvisation, some of it very sincere,

1628
01:04:56,467 --> 01:04:57,634
Fills the gaps.

1629
01:04:57,634 --> 01:04:59,000
It would have been easy

1630
01:04:59,000 --> 01:05:01,934
To falsify a
past back then--

1631
01:05:01,934 --> 01:05:05,300
A few words, credulity--
Time would do the rest.

1632
01:05:05,300 --> 01:05:07,467
Now you're talking as
if you believed him.

1633
01:05:07,467 --> 01:05:09,667
Well, look at the
popular myths surrounding

1634
01:05:09,667 --> 01:05:12,300
The Kennedy assassination
in a few short years--

1635
01:05:12,300 --> 01:05:15,767
You had, uh,
conspiracy, Mafia, CIA--

1636
01:05:15,767 --> 01:05:18,334
That's a mystique that'll never go away.

1637
01:05:18,334 --> 01:05:22,167
It's always been a small step
from a fallen leader to a god.

1638
01:05:22,167 --> 01:05:25,033
I don't think anybody
will deify kennedy.

1639
01:05:25,033 --> 01:05:27,000
We're more sophisticated than that.

1640
01:05:27,000 --> 01:05:28,534
We are?

1641
01:05:28,534 --> 01:05:30,167
We are.

1642
01:05:33,767 --> 01:05:35,400
Well, you're finally fulfilling

1643
01:05:35,400 --> 01:05:38,300
One prophecy about the millennium, John.

1644
01:05:38,300 --> 01:05:39,567
What's that?

1645
01:05:39,567 --> 01:05:42,133
Here you are again.

1646
01:05:51,701 --> 01:05:53,701
You like the fire, John.

1647
01:05:53,701 --> 01:05:57,200
Everywhere I've lived,
I've had a fireplace.

1648
01:05:57,200 --> 01:05:59,701
Childhood fixation, I guess.

1649
01:06:01,367 --> 01:06:03,400
Helps me to feel secure.

1650
01:06:04,801 --> 01:06:06,868
There are predators out there.

1651
01:06:09,300 --> 01:06:10,968
One thing I didn't pack...

1652
01:06:10,968 --> 01:06:12,934
I thought I might need it.

1653
01:06:14,100 --> 01:06:18,400
( Plays beethoven's 7th symphony )

1654
01:06:20,167 --> 01:06:23,467
<i>Wouldn't sacre du printemps
be more appropriate?</i>

1655
01:06:23,467 --> 01:06:24,534
What?

1656
01:06:26,167 --> 01:06:28,267
You've got...

1657
01:06:28,267 --> 01:06:31,434
four men of science
completely baffled, my friend.

1658
01:06:31,434 --> 01:06:34,033
We--We don't know
what to make of you.

1659
01:06:34,033 --> 01:06:36,801
Did you know voltaire
was the first to suggest

1660
01:06:36,801 --> 01:06:40,234
That the universe was created
by a gigantic explosion?

1661
01:06:40,234 --> 01:06:42,567
I think paul would agree.

1662
01:06:42,567 --> 01:06:45,033
And then goethe was the first to suggest

1663
01:06:45,033 --> 01:06:48,901
That spiral nebulae were
swirling masses of stars.

1664
01:06:48,901 --> 01:06:51,100
We now call them galaxies.

1665
01:06:51,100 --> 01:06:53,834
It's kind of funny how
often new concepts of science

1666
01:06:53,834 --> 01:06:56,734
Find their first tentative
forms of expression in the arts.

1667
01:06:56,734 --> 01:07:01,701
So did beethoven do physics on the side?

1668
01:07:01,701 --> 01:07:05,000
He spent most of his
time lying on the floor

1669
01:07:05,000 --> 01:07:06,734
In front of his legless piano

1670
01:07:06,734 --> 01:07:09,467
Surrounded by orange
peels and apple cores.

1671
01:07:11,634 --> 01:07:14,434
Now we're on the floor
listening to beethoven.

1672
01:07:15,701 --> 01:07:17,267
Full circle.

1673
01:07:17,267 --> 01:07:19,567
Did you have, um...

1674
01:07:20,667 --> 01:07:22,400
any religious beliefs,

1675
01:07:22,400 --> 01:07:25,033
Or did you give it much thought?

1676
01:07:25,033 --> 01:07:26,901
You can't get there with thought.

1677
01:07:26,901 --> 01:07:28,901
You have faith?

1678
01:07:28,901 --> 01:07:30,234
In a lot of things.

1679
01:07:30,234 --> 01:07:33,300
Do you have faith in
the future of the race?

1680
01:07:33,300 --> 01:07:35,300
I've seen species come and go.

1681
01:07:35,300 --> 01:07:37,367
Depends on their balance
with the environment.

1682
01:07:39,067 --> 01:07:40,767
We've made a mess of it.

1683
01:07:40,767 --> 01:07:42,400
There's still time,

1684
01:07:42,400 --> 01:07:44,167
If we use it well.

1685
01:07:44,167 --> 01:07:46,868
Christianity has been a worldwide belief

1686
01:07:46,868 --> 01:07:48,601
For 2,000 years.

1687
01:07:48,601 --> 01:07:50,801
How long did the egyptians worship isis

1688
01:07:50,801 --> 01:07:52,467
Or the sumerians ishtar?

1689
01:07:52,467 --> 01:07:55,100
In india, sacred cows wandered freely

1690
01:07:55,100 --> 01:07:56,968
As reincarnated souls.

1691
01:07:56,968 --> 01:07:58,734
In a thousand years,
they'll be barbecued

1692
01:07:58,734 --> 01:08:00,334
And their souls will be in squirrels.

1693
01:08:00,334 --> 01:08:01,701
You weren't Jesus!

1694
01:08:03,734 --> 01:08:04,934
Oh, Edith.

1695
01:08:07,734 --> 01:08:10,501
( Clears throat ) if
it rains... it won't.

1696
01:08:10,501 --> 01:08:11,701
How do you know that?

1697
01:08:11,701 --> 01:08:13,234
I don't smell it.

1698
01:08:16,701 --> 01:08:17,667
Were you...

1699
01:08:18,934 --> 01:08:21,167
I guess... a medicine man?

1700
01:08:21,167 --> 01:08:23,467
I was a shaman a few times.

1701
01:08:23,467 --> 01:08:26,801
I revealed some truths
to eat a little better.

1702
01:08:26,801 --> 01:08:29,868
You think that's all
religion is about...

1703
01:08:29,868 --> 01:08:32,467
selling hope and survival?

1704
01:08:32,467 --> 01:08:34,868
The old testament sells fear and guilt.

1705
01:08:34,868 --> 01:08:37,567
The new testament is
a good code of ethics,

1706
01:08:37,567 --> 01:08:40,033
Put into my mouth by
poets and philosophers

1707
01:08:40,033 --> 01:08:42,200
That are much smarter than I am.

1708
01:08:42,200 --> 01:08:44,200
The message is never practiced.

1709
01:08:45,367 --> 01:08:47,000
Fairy tales build churches.

1710
01:08:48,067 --> 01:08:50,334
What about the name "Jesus"?

1711
01:08:50,334 --> 01:08:52,367
Did you pull that out of a hat?

1712
01:08:52,367 --> 01:08:54,334
I called myself John.

1713
01:08:54,334 --> 01:08:57,067
I almost always do.

1714
01:08:57,067 --> 01:08:59,133
As tales of the resurrection spread,

1715
01:08:59,133 --> 01:09:01,901
<i>The name was confused
with the hebrew "yochanan,"</i>

1716
01:09:01,901 --> 01:09:03,767
Meaning "god is gracious."

1717
01:09:03,767 --> 01:09:05,567
My stay on earth was seen

1718
01:09:05,567 --> 01:09:08,234
As divine proof of immortality.

1719
01:09:08,234 --> 01:09:12,868
That led to "god is salvation"

1720
01:09:12,868 --> 01:09:14,400
<i>Or hebrew "yahshua,"</i>

1721
01:09:14,400 --> 01:09:17,567
Which in translation
became my proper name,

1722
01:09:17,567 --> 01:09:20,467
<i>Changing to late greek, "iesous,"</i>

1723
01:09:20,467 --> 01:09:22,801
<i>Then to late latin, "iesus,"</i>

1724
01:09:22,801 --> 01:09:25,434
And finally medieval latin, "Jesus,"

1725
01:09:25,434 --> 01:09:28,167
And it was a wonder
to watch it all happen.

1726
01:09:28,167 --> 01:09:31,367
Then you didn't claim
to be the son of god?

1727
01:09:31,367 --> 01:09:34,667
Began as a schoolhouse
and ended as a temple.

1728
01:09:34,667 --> 01:09:38,234
I said I had a master that
was greater than myself.

1729
01:09:38,234 --> 01:09:40,234
I never said he was my father.

1730
01:09:40,234 --> 01:09:42,234
I wanted to teach what I learned.

1731
01:09:42,234 --> 01:09:44,334
I never claimed to be king of the jews,

1732
01:09:44,334 --> 01:09:47,467
I never walked on water,
I never raised the dead.

1733
01:09:47,467 --> 01:09:50,801
I never spoke of divine
except in the sense

1734
01:09:50,801 --> 01:09:52,968
Of human goodness on earth.

1735
01:09:56,501 --> 01:10:00,100
No wise men came from the
east to worship at a manger.

1736
01:10:00,100 --> 01:10:02,267
I did do a little healing

1737
01:10:02,267 --> 01:10:04,100
With some eastern medicine I'd learned.

1738
01:10:06,901 --> 01:10:08,000
That's it.

1739
01:10:11,801 --> 01:10:14,000
The three wise men began as a myth

1740
01:10:14,000 --> 01:10:15,567
About the birth of the Buddha.

1741
01:10:20,300 --> 01:10:24,267
John, I should be home,
uh, kissing my wife.

1742
01:10:26,467 --> 01:10:28,634
We're all here, trapped by your story...

1743
01:10:30,100 --> 01:10:35,868
hoping for a...revolution? I don't know.

1744
01:10:39,200 --> 01:10:41,334
Are there any, uh...

1745
01:10:41,334 --> 01:10:43,100
more revelations for us?

1746
01:10:49,567 --> 01:10:51,467
It's just like old times.

1747
01:10:58,100 --> 01:11:00,067
You weren't Jesus.

1748
01:11:02,968 --> 01:11:05,267
Quote the sermon on the mount.

1749
01:11:05,267 --> 01:11:06,601
Which one?

1750
01:11:06,601 --> 01:11:09,801
Darby, King James,
New American Standard?

1751
01:11:09,801 --> 01:11:11,701
Do you know them all?

1752
01:11:11,701 --> 01:11:14,868
No one knows the one, not even me.

1753
01:11:14,868 --> 01:11:16,234
I...

1754
01:11:16,234 --> 01:11:18,534
I did some teaching on a hill one day.

1755
01:11:18,534 --> 01:11:20,601
Not that many people stayed.

1756
01:11:20,601 --> 01:11:21,767
But you...

1757
01:11:21,767 --> 01:11:23,801
biblical Jesus said,

1758
01:11:23,801 --> 01:11:27,033
"Who do you think I am?"

1759
01:11:27,033 --> 01:11:28,667
He gave them a choice.

1760
01:11:30,200 --> 01:11:31,567
I'm giving you one.

1761
01:11:34,534 --> 01:11:35,901
Were you?

1762
01:11:37,901 --> 01:11:40,534
If I said no, could you ever be sure?

1763
01:11:48,934 --> 01:11:50,567
( Sobs )

1764
01:11:57,701 --> 01:11:59,634
Turn that off.

1765
01:11:59,634 --> 01:12:00,601
Please.

1766
01:12:03,701 --> 01:12:05,801
This has gone far enough.

1767
01:12:05,801 --> 01:12:07,734
It's gone much too far.

1768
01:12:07,734 --> 01:12:10,067
These people are very upset.

1769
01:12:10,067 --> 01:12:12,834
I don't believe you're mad,

1770
01:12:12,834 --> 01:12:15,133
But what you're saying is not true.

1771
01:12:16,234 --> 01:12:19,067
That leaves only one explanation.

1772
01:12:20,234 --> 01:12:22,334
The time has come when you must admit

1773
01:12:22,334 --> 01:12:23,534
This is a hoax...

1774
01:12:25,234 --> 01:12:26,534
a lie.

1775
01:12:26,534 --> 01:12:30,200
Isn't that true, John?

1776
01:12:30,200 --> 01:12:32,968
If you don't drop
this now-- If you can--

1777
01:12:32,968 --> 01:12:34,534
I'll be convinced

1778
01:12:34,534 --> 01:12:37,400
That you need a great deal of attention.

1779
01:12:37,400 --> 01:12:40,434
I can have you committed
for observation.

1780
01:12:40,434 --> 01:12:41,734
You know that.

1781
01:12:41,734 --> 01:12:43,734
I ask
you now--

1782
01:12:43,734 --> 01:12:45,968
I demand
it--

1783
01:12:45,968 --> 01:12:49,033
That you tell these people the truth.

1784
01:12:49,033 --> 01:12:52,801
Give them closure.

1785
01:12:52,801 --> 01:12:55,567
It's time, John.

1786
01:12:55,567 --> 01:12:56,767
Please.

1787
01:13:10,434 --> 01:13:13,200
End of the line. Everybody off.

1788
01:13:16,467 --> 01:13:18,467
What?!

1789
01:13:18,467 --> 01:13:20,300
It was a story.

1790
01:13:20,300 --> 01:13:22,734
It was all a story.

1791
01:13:22,734 --> 01:13:23,734
( Sobs )

1792
01:13:23,734 --> 01:13:24,667
Good god!

1793
01:13:26,467 --> 01:13:27,767
Another fairy tale?

1794
01:13:27,767 --> 01:13:30,033
All of it?
But what--

1795
01:13:30,033 --> 01:13:31,434
What in the name of heaven...

1796
01:13:31,434 --> 01:13:33,667
John, you had us wondering
whether you were sane or not,

1797
01:13:33,667 --> 01:13:35,300
And it's just a story!

1798
01:13:35,300 --> 01:13:38,601
Where'd you come off with such
a half-baked, asinine idea?

1799
01:13:38,601 --> 01:13:40,400
At least you're relieved I'm not a nut.

1800
01:13:40,400 --> 01:13:41,901
I'd prefer you were!

1801
01:13:41,901 --> 01:13:43,701
You gave me the idea.

1802
01:13:43,701 --> 01:13:45,000
All of you.

1803
01:13:45,000 --> 01:13:46,467
Come again?

1804
01:13:46,467 --> 01:13:48,033
Edith saw my fake Van Gogh.

1805
01:13:48,033 --> 01:13:49,601
You could have just told me.

1806
01:13:49,601 --> 01:13:50,901
You commented that I never age.

1807
01:13:50,901 --> 01:13:52,701
You gave me the book on early man.

1808
01:13:52,701 --> 01:13:54,334
Dan, you spotted the burin

1809
01:13:54,334 --> 01:13:56,000
And you said, "if stones could speak."

1810
01:13:56,000 --> 01:13:57,667
I knew it.

1811
01:13:57,667 --> 01:14:00,133
I got the notion, I ran it past you

1812
01:14:00,133 --> 01:14:02,701
To check your reactions,
and I took it too far.

1813
01:14:02,701 --> 01:14:04,100
Too far?

1814
01:14:04,100 --> 01:14:05,601
Check my reaction.

1815
01:14:05,601 --> 01:14:08,167
You asked if I was a figure
from religious history,

1816
01:14:08,167 --> 01:14:09,734
If there were others like me,

1817
01:14:09,734 --> 01:14:11,167
If I'd created future identities.

1818
01:14:11,167 --> 01:14:14,267
We were chasing our
tails around the maypole,

1819
01:14:14,267 --> 01:14:17,467
Enjoying the mystery,
the analytical stretch.

1820
01:14:17,467 --> 01:14:19,400
You were playing my game!

1821
01:14:19,400 --> 01:14:21,000
I was playing yours.

1822
01:14:21,000 --> 01:14:23,601
Oh, man, you know, you
had us going, right?

1823
01:14:23,601 --> 01:14:24,868
You were good, man.

1824
01:14:24,868 --> 01:14:26,367
You know those chinese boxes,

1825
01:14:26,367 --> 01:14:29,434
One inside the other inside
the other inside the other--

1826
01:14:29,434 --> 01:14:32,501
I feel like I'm in the last box.

1827
01:14:32,501 --> 01:14:34,801
You son of a...

1828
01:14:34,801 --> 01:14:35,868
bitch!

1829
01:14:35,868 --> 01:14:37,400
How could you do this to us?

1830
01:14:37,400 --> 01:14:39,501
I was worried about you.

1831
01:14:39,501 --> 01:14:41,934
I know, I was tempted
to cop out many times,

1832
01:14:41,934 --> 01:14:44,200
But I couldn't resist
seeing whether or not

1833
01:14:44,200 --> 01:14:45,968
You could refute what I was saying.

1834
01:14:45,968 --> 01:14:47,467
I had the
perfect audience--

1835
01:14:47,467 --> 01:14:49,801
Anthropologist, archaeologist,

1836
01:14:49,801 --> 01:14:51,901
Christian literalist...

1837
01:14:51,901 --> 01:14:54,100
a psychologist.

1838
01:14:54,100 --> 01:14:56,200
Okay, I've had enough of this.

1839
01:14:56,200 --> 01:14:58,267
I'm outta here. You
wanna come? Let's go.

1840
01:14:59,400 --> 01:15:00,667
So, John.

1841
01:15:00,667 --> 01:15:02,167
Are you gonna write the story?

1842
01:15:02,167 --> 01:15:03,868
If I do, I'll send you copies.

1843
01:15:03,868 --> 01:15:05,501
Don't bother with mine, okay?

1844
01:15:05,501 --> 01:15:08,367
You are absolutely certifiable.

1845
01:15:08,367 --> 01:15:10,100
I don't know you!

1846
01:15:12,467 --> 01:15:14,801
It was nice seeing
you again, Dr. Oldman.

1847
01:15:16,234 --> 01:15:18,033
Your name's a pun, isn't it?

1848
01:15:18,033 --> 01:15:19,033
Old man?

1849
01:15:20,901 --> 01:15:23,501
Did that help you with your story?

1850
01:15:23,501 --> 01:15:25,133
Linda!

1851
01:15:26,767 --> 01:15:27,834
